      "id": "PopularPost284709",
      "post_content": "Always better than lava axe.  \nFirst: This is an instant. You can use it at the end of your opponents turn.  \nSecond: This protects against mill. Buy's you a turn after [Painter's Servant](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Painter's Servant) and [Grindstone](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Grindstone).  \nThird: This can target creatures.   \nForth: I use Lava Axe as kindling.  \n ",
      "posted_by": "twiddleman12",
